cratization in the twentieth. He also sheds light on the modern history of Latin America as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh  a19th century.  acocaine wars.  acocaine.  acolombia.  adictators.  adrug cartel.  adrug trafficking.  aeconomic growth.  aeconomy.  aemeralds.  aexports.  agovernment.  aguerrilla warfare.  ahistory of colombia.  aindependence.  aindustrialization.  ainternational.  alarge countries.  alatin america.  aliterature.  amilitary.  apolitical.  apolitics.  apopulation.  apopulist movement.  apopulist.  aprecious gems.  areform.  asouth america.  astereotypes.  aurbanization.  aviolence.  awar on drugs.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091390540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520913905423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520913905/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles